      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Features decreasing hERG blockade likelihood**\n- **Two phenolic OH groups:** These increase **polarity** and can reduce effective hydrophobicity/logD, potentially lowering passive membrane accumulation and weakening purely hydrophobic binding. They can also increase solvation penalty upon binding.\n- **Not strongly \u201ctwo-aromatic-wings on a flexible linker\u201d:** Some potent hERG blockers exploit flexibility to optimize cavity fit; this molecule is more rigid and bulky, which could either help (preorganization) or hurt (steric mismatch).",
      "tool_name": null,
